[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    141[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Problem:** Same chapter pattern as 11.4 Finding S2 with recipe-distinct PFI-as-additionally-sensitive amplification and state-insurance-retention-floor extension. The recipe correctly elevates the benefits-decision-record-journal as the durable answer-record-equivalent for benefits answers and the conversation log as dense PHI plus financial information. Despite this elevation, the architecture pattern, the diagram, and the pseudocode treat the benefits-decision-record-journal write and the tool-call-ledger writes as embedding rather than referencing the per-conversation content. Recipe-acute and recipe-distinct because:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    142[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    143[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   1. **The benefits-decision-record-journal is the recipe's load-bearing combined-PHI-and-PFI record artifact.** Object Lock in compliance mode for the audit-pipeline retention window aligns with the audit pipeline retention; the benefits-decision-record-journal also has state-insurance-retention obligations that may be longer than the audit-pipeline retention floor (per-state insurance records retention rules vary; some are 7 years, some 10 years for plan-records, some include specific retention timelines for dispute records and appeal records). The recipe's ERISA-and-state-insurance-law scope makes this recipe-acute. The architecture should specify the per-state insurance-records retention floor reconciliation and the per-record-class retention regime distinct from the audit-archive.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    144[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    145[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   2. **The decision_record's question_text, answer_text, citations array, and regulatory_disclosures_included are combined-PHI-and-PFI elements with their own retention and access-control profiles.** The question_text contains medical questions inferable from procedures and medications; the answer_text contains coverage determinations, cost estimates, denial reasons, and regulatory-rights-and-obligations content; the citations array contains references to plan-document chunks that may identify specific plan-document version and section that forms the basis for the answer; the regulatory_disclosures_included contains state-specific complaint-rights and appeal-rights content. Some elements are part of the formal benefits-administration record at some institutions; some are part of the audit-pipeline-by-others; each element has its own retention and access-control profile.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    146[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    147[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   3. **The cost-estimate responses include per-claim adjudication detail that is PFI plus PHI.** The cost_estimate response includes deductible_applied, coinsurance_applied, copay, OOP-max_impact, breakdown_by_service, accumulator_state_at_estimate, negotiated_rate_used. Each is dense financial information plus medical-context. Some states' consumer-financial-information rules add layers of protection. The architecture should specify the per-element access-control surface.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    148[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    149[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   4. **The patient's natural-language utterances throughout benefits-navigation are potentially-financial-distress-sensitive.** A member mentioning inability-to-pay, financial hardship, threatened bankruptcy, or domestic-violence-related access-control concerns embeds the disclosure in the conversation log and possibly in the structured intent. The architecture should specify the per-disclosure-class handling (sensitive disclosures route to a separately-governed sensitive-disclosure surface with restricted access).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    150[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    151[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   5. **The conversation log is dense PHI plus financial information.** The recipe's prose correctly elevates this. The architecture should specify the per-record-class retention reconciliation (audit-archive retention vs benefits-decision-record-journal retention vs conversation-log retention vs version-stamp-registry retention may differ; some institutions treat the conversation log as part of the benefits-administration record while others treat it as an audit-pipeline artifact; some state insurance laws specifically address consumer-communication retention).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    152[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    153[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   6. **The per-record-class access-control surface is not specified.** The audit pipeline's access-control surface is the audit-and-compliance team plus the privacy officer. The benefits-decision-record-journal's access-control surface is the benefits-administration team plus the compliance team plus the appeals-and-grievances team plus the audit-and-compliance team plus the member-services-team retrospective reviewers plus the member (through portal access). The version-stamp-registry's access-control surface is the engineering team plus the audit-and-compliance team for incident review. The tool-call-ledger's access-control surface is the engineering team plus the audit-and-compliance team for incident review. Each record class has different access-control needs.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    154[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    155[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   7. **The cross-correlation with the institution's claims-system-of-record and FHIR ExplanationOfBenefit records is recipe-distinct.** The cost_estimate_compute tool reads from negotiated-rate database and the cost-share-rule registry; the claim_lookup tool reads from the claims-system-of-record (or HealthLake's FHIR ExplanationOfBenefit) ; the institution's claims-system retention obligations apply alongside the benefits-decision-record-journal's retention. The architecture should specify the cross-system reconciliation discipline.
