[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    646[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Recipe 11.5 is publishable at the medium-tier level once the three HIGH findings are closed. The Honest Take is the recipe's strongest single passage and the chapter's strongest single articulation of the regulatory-exposure-most-dispersed-across-federal-and-state-authorities primitive in benefits-navigation context. The "Aaron's bill problem, and the front-desk staff problem of telling Aaron's wife what the MRI will cost before she has it, are two sides of the same data integration" framing matches the chapter pattern from 11.1, 11.2, 11.3, and 11.4 while elevating the recipe-distinct benefits-navigator contributions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    647[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    648[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The recipe-specific contributions that should be elevated to the chapter preface as load-bearing primitives are: (a) the **plan-document-corpus-with-versioned-governance-organized-per-plan-and-per-plan-year primitive** (recipe-distinct, load-bearing for any benefits-navigator conversational AI recipe; the corpus is the bot's coverage-answer-quality ceiling); (b) the **regulatory-disclosure-phrasings-library-with-state-specific-configurations-and-named-compliance-ownership primitive** (recipe-distinct, load-bearing; state insurance laws plus federal rules plus per-line-of-business rules layer onto every member communication); (c) the **cost-share-rule-registry-as-code primitive** (recipe-distinct, load-bearing; the cost-estimate math runs as deterministic code over the registry, not as LLM arithmetic); (d) the **CARC/RARC-translation-library-with-typically-appeal-flag primitive** (recipe-distinct; the library is the load-bearing semantic layer between machine-readable adjudication codes and member-facing language); (e) the **citation-grounding-as-launch-gate-not-post-launch-dashboard primitive** (recipe-distinct, load-bearing; the citation-coverage-rate metric is a launch-gate threshold, not a post-launch dashboard); (f) the **cost-estimate-accuracy-as-trust-acute-metric primitive** (recipe-distinct; a member quoted $500 who gets a bill for $1,800 will not trust the bot again; conservative estimates with explicit ranges and caveats are the standard pattern); (g) the **ancillary-provider-vs-facility-distinction-for-No-Surprises-Act primitive** (recipe-distinct; the bot's network-status answer for facility queries must include the ancillary-warning explicitly); (h) the **parity-aware-coverage-logic-for-behavioral-health primitive** (recipe-distinct; misstating a behavioral-health benefit is a parity-law violation); (i) the **member-services-routing-with-full-case-context-handoff primitive** (recipe-distinct; a bot that says "I can't help with that, please call us" without connecting the conversation context makes the member-services call worse, not better); (j) the **conversation-log-as-dense-PHI-plus-PFI primitive** (recipe-distinct; the conversation contains medical history inferable from procedures and medications plus financial information that some state laws treat with additional sensitivity); (k) the **Aaron-as-canonical-user-and-canonical-surprise-bill-scenario primitive** (recipe-distinct; the canonical case grounds the recipe's moral case for the project); (l) the **two-sides-of-the-same-data-integration primitive** (recipe-distinct; the payer-side member-facing deployment and the provider-side front-desk-facing deployment share the architecture; building for both doubles the operational impact); (m) the **integration-layer-as-engineering-effort-concentration primitive** (recipe-distinct; the wrappers around the eligibility, claims, accumulator, UM, formulary, and provider-network systems are where the engineering value lives, not the LLM layer).
